============ One time settings ==================

git config --global user.name ==> sets the username of whoever will be using git.

git config --global user.email ==> sets the email address of whoever will be using git.


===================Actual git commands =========================

git init ==> tells git to start tracking this folder.

git clone ==> copy work from the remote server

git status ==> checks for the current state of our repository or folder.

git add .(dot) ==> all everything to git's waiting area

git add git-commands ==> add only a file called git-commands to git's waiting area.

git commit -m "messages meaning messages" ==>  describes the changes be saved.


git branch ==> displays / lists out all the branchs in our git repository.

git push ==> sends your copy of the work to the remote server.

git pull ==> downloads work from the remote server to your local computer


README.md ==> tells people what your repo is all about.